# Automata - Ride Booking Automation App

## Phase 1: Project Foundation & UI
- [ ] Set up Jetpack Compose with Material 3
- [ ] Create data models (Task, TaskConfig, SavedLocation, RideApp)
- [ ] Create local database with Room for persisting settings
- [ ] Build main dashboard screen (task list with "Go" button)
- [ ] Build task configuration screen (ride booking settings)
- [ ] Build settings screen (saved locations, preferences)

## Phase 2: Accessibility Service Core & Step Engine
- [ ] Create `AutomataAccessibilityService` extending `AccessibilityService`
- [ ] Configure accessibility service metadata XML
- [ ] Add permissions & service declaration to AndroidManifest
- [ ] Build node-finding utility helpers (find by text, ID, class)
- [ ] Build action execution helpers (click, setText, scroll)
- [ ] Build step sequencer — define automation as a list of Steps (waitForScreen → action → waitForResult) with per-step timeouts and retry logic
- [ ] Build state machine (Idle → Running → WaitingForUI → StepComplete → Error → Done) to track automation progress
- [ ] Add error recovery: stuck-detection (step timeout exceeded), back-out strategy (press back, return to known state), and graceful abort

## Phase 3: First App End-to-End (PickMe)
- [ ] Add PickMe layout/version detection (verify expected UI elements exist before proceeding)
- [ ] Create PickMe automation script as a Step sequence (launch → set destination → select bike → get price)
- [ ] Add persistent notification showing automation status
- [ ] Add ride confirmation detection via NotificationListenerService
- [ ] Test full PickMe pipeline on device end-to-end (including confirmation & status updates)

## Phase 4: Second App & Orchestrator (Uber)
- [ ] Add Uber layout/version detection
- [ ] Create Uber automation script as a Step sequence
- [ ] Test Uber pipeline on device end-to-end
- [ ] Build orchestrator that runs both apps sequentially (PickMe then Uber), collects prices
- [ ] Implement decision logic (cheapest price vs fastest confirmation)
- [ ] Implement auto-cancel of losing app once ride is confirmed in winning app

## Phase 5: Testing & Polish
- [ ] Edge case handling (app not installed, no rides available, network error, UI changed unexpectedly)
- [ ] Full two-app orchestration testing on device
- [ ] Build walkthrough / first-run setup guide
